cs.NA, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.SC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper deals with multiple precision arithmetic and presents a new adaptable numeric core inspired by floating point expansions and on-line arithmetic. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper mentions the use of the Coq assistant to formally check the correctness of the proofs. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper discusses the development of application-specific adaptable libraries based on the toolset. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper presents a new toolset for arithmetic operations, which can be seen as a data structure. 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation): The paper mentions the formal proofs of many results published in the literature, which can be seen as symbolic computation.
